Ingredients:
1 pound of chicken tenders
Cajun seasoning
Creole seasoning 
1 jalapeño 
Garlic purée 
Sundried tomatoes
Pasta of your choice
Parmesan cheese 
1 cup of heavy cream
Salt to taste

Directions:
Cook pasta per package directions but reserve half a cup of the pasta water
Season chicken with copious amounts of the seasonings 
Sauté chicken until cooked thru, has a beautiful crust, and left a flavorful fond
In the fond, sauté a teaspoon of garlic purée then add your diced jalapeño and sundried tomatoes 
Deglaze the pan with the pasta water, add some heavy cream and season once more
Add an unthinkable amount of Parmesan cheese to the sauce and let thicken
Toss the pasta and the chicken back into the pan and stir 
Plate up with more cheese, say bismillah, and enjoy!

@nick.digiovanni Challenged me for a Chicken and Rice off, who won? 🤤

Chicken Mandi 

Ingredients:
1 whole chicken
3 cups basmati rice
2 shallots
2 jalapenos
2 bay leaves
A few cardamom pods
Ghee/clarified butter 
1 teaspoon garlic paste
1 teaspoon ginger paste
Spice Mix:
¼ teaspoon Cumin
1 teaspoon Cayenne pepper
½ teaspoon Ground clove
2 teaspoons Turmeric
½ teaspoon Coriander seed
½ teaspoon Cinnamon 
½ teaspoon Ground ginger
1 teaspoon Allspice
1 teaspoon Ground cardamom 
Salsa:
2 bunches of cilantro
2 tomatoes
2 jalapenos
A few cloves of garlic
1 tablespoon of olive oil
Salt to taste

Directions: 
In a bowl combine 2 tablespoons of ghee, the garlic and ginger pastes, salt and pepper to taste, and 1 tablespoon of the spice mix
Remove the spine from the chicken then rub with the spice paste
In an oven safe pot, saute the shallots and jalapenos, add 1 tablespoon of the spice mix, bay leaves and cardamom pods in a 2 tablespoons of ghee
Once everything is toasted and aromatic, add the washed rice, mix, and add water
*add a few extra tablespoons of water than what's listed on the package since more moisture is going to be lost in the oven
Place a wire over the rice pot and lay the chicken on top of that. This allows all those flavorful drippings to get caught in the rice
Bake at 375 for roughly 50 minutes to 1 hour but make sure to check the internal temperature since cooking time may vary depending on the size of the chicken
*If you want to smoke the chicken/rice, drop the chicken into the pot, place a heat proof bowl with a few tablespoons of oil in there as well, drop a charcoal and cover
For the salsa, rough chop the vegetables then blend with the rest of the ingredients
Plate up the rice, place the chicken on top, salsa to the side, say bismillah, and enjoy!

Beef Ribs 😈 

2 slabs of beef ribs 
Apply Mustard thoroughly 

Bbq Rub: 
1 Tbsp brown sugar 
2 tsp onion, garlic, chili, paprika 
1 tsp cayenne pepper 
2 tsp salt 
1 tsp thyme 

I used a good quality bbq sauce, you can easily make your own. 

Cover in foil and bake at 300F for about 2 1/2 hours - 3 hours (190 Internal) 

Cover in bbq sauce and broil for about 5-10 minutes. Let them rest before cutting into them and enjoy😭

Jammin Jalapeño 😈

2 lbs chicken wings 

1 Tbsp jalapeño dust 
2 tsp baking powder 
2 tsp salt 

Air fry at 400F for around 20 minutes flipping mid way through. 
Oven bake at 415F for 20-30 minutes if you’d like 

Sauce:
3-4 tbsp butter 
Juice and zest of 2 limes 
2 tbsp jalapeño dust 
2 tbsp honey 
Salt to taste

node.text:
Honey Sriracha Wings 😍

To 1 lb chicken Wings
Marinade in 1-2 cups butter milk 
Seasoning: 2 tsp salt, cayenne, onion, garlic and paprika (the standard) 

Dry batter: 
1 cup rice flour (or regular) 
1 cup potato starch (or corn) 
1 tsp cayenne 
2 tsp paprika, onion, garlic powder 
1-2 tsp salt to taste 

First fry at 315F for about 6-7 minutes. Let them rest as the fryer goes up to 375F and finish them off for about 2-3 more minutes until Crispy!

Sauce:
1/2 cup sriracha 
1/4 cup honey 
2 Tbsp mayo (I used kewpie) 

Chives make it healthy of course

Superior Kebab Sandwich 😈

For 6 kebabs: 

1 lb Ground beef or lamb 
1 tsp garlic & onion powder
2 tsp smoked paprika
1/2 tsp cayenne
1/2 tsp all spice
1 tsp salt

1 jalapeño 
1 tomato 
1/2 white onion 
1/2 cup cilantro or parsley 
1 Roma tomato 
1/4 cup feta cheese 

White sauce:
1 cup full fat yogurt 
1/4 sesame paste 
1/2 lemon juice and zest 
2 Tbsp vinegar 
Salt to taste 

3 pitas 

Finish with potato crisps if you’re petty and a mix of raw parsley and white onions

Garlic Noodle Shrimp 😍

8 oz Shrimp 
8 oz Noodles of choice (I used nam yung)
Tempura: 
3/4 cup rice flour (or regular flour) 
3/4 cup starch (potato or corn) 
Around 8oz water 

Spices:
2 tsp garlic powder, cayenne pepper, chili powder, paprika, onion powder
Salt to taste (I used around 2 tsp)

1/2 of the spices go into the dry batter, and half on the shrimp 

4 oz butter 
10 cloves of garlic 
1/4 cup soy sauce 
2 Tbsp eel sauce 

Finish with green onions, chives, parsley or cilantro 🥰

Simple Chili Glazed Salmon 🤤

8 oz salmon 
2 tbsp honey 
2 Tbsp fried chilis in oil 
2 tsp rice vinegar 
Salt to taste

Air fry for 5 minutes, brush more marinade on and air fry for 3-5 more minutes depending on how thick the salmon is! 

This is just a quick salmon idea I was craving. The sides are all up to you! When I’m not specific about something, that means it doesn’t matter what you use!

Tuna Melt 😍

8 slices bread 
3 Tuna cans (113g) (Starkist albacore Chunk Light tuna in water)
1/4 cup celery 
1/3 cup red onion 
1 jalapeño 
1/4 cup mayo (I used kewpie) 
2 teaspoons creole seasoning 
Zest and juice of a lemon 
1/4 cup chopped cilantro 
Cheese of choice (I used spicy havarti) 
Hot peppers to taste 

Makes about 4 sandwiches!
